meta {
  name: [APISIX] allow BRP read - valid JWT, valid purpose
  type: http
  seq: 5
}

docs {
  EXPECTED behaviour once the auth-zen APISIX plugin is implemented.

  The plugin should:
    1. Extract the subject from the Bearer JWT (sub, organization, assurance_level, roles, scopes).
    2. Map the HTTP method (GET) to action "read" and the request path to the resource.
    3. Call the AuthZEN policy agent with the full evaluation input.
    4. Forward the request to the upstream when the decision is "allow".

  The JWT payload used here decodes to:
    { "sub": "municipality-case-api", "organization": "urn:nl:gov:rotterdam",
      "assurance_level": "substantial", "roles": ["municipality_caseworker"],
      "scopes": ["brp:read"] }
}

get {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/anything
  body: none
}

